page.title: 15CROY WILDLIFE
page.content: In Croy there are many trees which stretch for miles.In these woods there are many animals such as fox,rabbit and squirrels.There are many differant kinds of birds too like the blue tit,robin,crow etc.In the woods you find game birds such as the pheasant.There are very many of these in Croy woods.You also hear woodpeckers and cuckoos but you can never see them.There is a river just outside Croy which is part of the Nairn River.You can catch brown trout and salmon in there.There are many ponds in Croy as well where you can see newts,tadpoles,frogs,toads,pondskaters ,water boatmen,water scorpions and great diving beetles.
